    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThere is no way to globally set a custom `vim.lsp.ListOpts`. For example to set `on_list` handler lsp commands such as `vim.lsp.buf.references()`. Today this requires remapping default key maps in order to pass the options parameter. I.e.\n\n```lua\nlocal on_list = function() ... end\n\nvim.keymap.del('n', 'grr')\nvim.keymap.set('n', 'grr', function() vim.lsp.buf.references({on_list = on_list) end, {})\n-- then repeat for other commands implementation, type_definition, definition, etc\n```\n\non_list was added back in 0.8, back then we did not have default key maps for go to locations commands. Back then users had to set all key maps themselves anyway and this issue wasn't adding too much friction. See #19213\n\nFor the same reason 3rd party plugins now provide custom functions or commands to show fuzzy pickers when multiple locations are returned. See [telescope](https://github.com/nvim-telescope/telescope.nvim#neovim-lsp-pickers) or [snacks.nvim](https://github.com/folke/snacks.nvim/blob/main/docs/picker.md#lsp_declarations)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nA default `on_list` handler can be set once which is used for all lsp location commands",
